    <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Written in 656/1258, the Gulistān is Saʻdī's most famous work, composed in rhymed prose with many verses interspersed throughout. The work, which is usually divided into eight sections, constists of entertaining anecdotes that
    illustrate ethical points.</subfield>
    </datafield>
