    <datafield tag="545" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Famous Ṣufī poet, Shaykh Abū ʻAbd allāh Musharrifu' al-Dīn bin Muṣiḥ Saʻdī; born in Shīrāz at the end of the 12th century. Lived for a time in Baghdad where he was influenced by
  Suhravardī. Traveled extensively, but eventually returned to Shīrāz, where he wrote his most famous works, the Gulistān and the Bustān, and eventually died in 691/1292.</subfield>
